
.TH NEONSEC-SUPPRESS 5 "2025-09-05" "neonsec" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
neonsec-suppress \- Pattern file for suppressing findings
.SH DESCRIPTION
Each non-empty, non-comment line contains `type:key` with glob wildcards `*` and `?`.
`type` or `key` may be `*` to match any. Examples:
  portscan:*
  *:10.0.*
  dns_*:*.corp.local
Use with \fB--suppress-file FILE\fR or inline via \fB--suppress 'type:key'\fR.
